Hi.
Why this should be in incubator?
id2Dir is a project specific function besides it can be rewritten much simpler.
Something like this.

``` php
function id2Dir($uniqueId)
{
    $result = str_pad($uniqueId, 10, '0', STR_PAD_LEFT);
    $result = substr($result, 0, 7) . '/' . substr($result, -3);
    $result = substr($result, 0, 4) . '/' . substr($result, 4);

    // id2Dir(123456) outputs "0000/123/456"

    return $result;
}
```

Also your implementation of truncateText doesn't work properly with multibyte strings.

I've found «truncateText» implementation in my project.
Maybe you test it and make new PR with it?

``` php
/**
 * Smart string truncate.
 * Splits string with max $maxNbWords or $maxNbChars.
 *
 * @param  string  $value
 * @param  integer $maxNbWords
 * @param  integer $maxNbChars
 * @param  string  $suffix
 * @return string
 */
public function getTruncated($value, $maxNbWords, $maxNbChars = 35, $suffix = '…')
{
    $unwantedCharsAtTheEnd = '#[\s\.\,]*$#u';
    $charset               = 'UTF-8';
    $suffixLength          = mb_strlen($suffix, $charset);

    $tokens    = preg_split('#[/\\\\\_\s]+#u', $value, $maxNbWords + 1);
    $nbTokens  = count($tokens);
    $padSuffix = false;

    if ($nbTokens > $maxNbWords) {
        $nbTokens  = $maxNbWords;
        $tokens    = array_slice($tokens, 0, $maxNbWords);
        $padSuffix = true;
    }

    $result = preg_replace($unwantedCharsAtTheEnd, "", implode(' ', $tokens)) . ($padSuffix ? $suffix : '');
    if ($maxNbChars <= $suffixLength || mb_strlen($result, $charset) <= $maxNbChars) {
        return $result;
    }

    while ($nbTokens > 1) {
        $last   = array_pop($tokens);
        $length = mb_strlen($result, $charset) - mb_strlen($last, $charset) - 1 - $suffixLength;
        $result = preg_replace($unwantedCharsAtTheEnd, "", mb_substr($result, 0, $length, $charset)) . $suffix;

        if (mb_strlen($result, $charset) <= $maxNbChars) {
            return $result;
        }

        --$nbTokens;
    }

    $result = preg_replace(
        $unwantedCharsAtTheEnd,
        "",
        mb_substr($result, 0, $maxNbChars - $suffixLength, $charset)
    ) . $suffix;

    return $result;
}
```

